## GIT / GITHUB

### Golden Rule: Use SSH, not HTTPS

HTTPS tokens expire or have scope limitations. SSH is the only reliable method
for headless servers. See `docs/github-ssh-setup.md`.

```bash
# Start SSH agent before any git push
eval $(ssh-agent -s)
ssh-add ~/.ssh/YOUR_KEY_NAME
ssh -T git@github.com  # Should show "Hi YOUR_USERNAME!"
```

---

## WORKING RULES

1. Never break Hermes config — restart `hermes-gateway.service` after changes
2. Check OpenRouter credit limits — cap `max_tokens` if needed
3. Don't bundle yt-dlp into PyInstaller — always use system binary

